the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Raymes was born about 1208, in Aydon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. She married Robert Raymes in 1229, in Aydon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"abt 1208–":"umbes 1208–Surnud","1206–Male":"1206–Surnud","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1208–Female":"1208–Surnud","1206":"1206","abt 1208":"umbes 1208","1230":"1230","1208":"1208","1229":"1229","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Aydon, Northumberland, England":"Aydon, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Aydon, Nrthmb, Engl":"Aydon, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1208–":"noin 1208–Kuollut","1206–Male":"1206–Kuollut","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1208–Female":"1208–Kuollut","1206":"1206","abt 1208":"noin 1208","1230":"1230","1208":"1208","1229":"1229","about 1230":"noin 1230","Aydon, Northumberland, England":"Aydon, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Aydon, Nrthmb, Engl":"Aydon, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1208–":"environ 1208–Décédée","1206–Male":"1206–Décédé","1230–Male":"1230–Décédé","1208–Female":"1208–Décédée","1206":"1206","abt 1208":"environ 1208","1230":"1230","1208":"1208","1229":"1229","about 1230":"environ 1230","Aydon, Northumberland, England":"Aydon, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Aydon, Nrthmb, Engl":"Aydon, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Raymes est née environ 1208, à Aydon, No